Biochemist, Systems Biologist and Data Scientist

Hello, I am currently a PhD Candidate at Vanderbilt University in the Chemical and Physical Biology PhD Program. I am interested in understanding how cells respond to stimulation in temporally changing environments.

How do temporal changes of stress in the environment control cell fate?

In particular, I am interested in understanding how cells sense, integrate and respond to environmental stress. In the context of my PhD work in the lab of my PhD advisor Gregor Neuert, I study the effect of gradual increases of extracellular stress on cells. I focus on the effect of increasing hypertonicity on cells a fundamental stress affecting cells in many tissues. Since the existence of life, cells had to cope with changes in extracellular hypertonicity and therefore mechanisms and even pathway components responding to the stress are conserved from bacteria to humans.

Currently, I am preparing a manuscript[1] in which I describe the results of my studies in human cells. I investigated the effect of dynamically changing NaCl inputs on cellular processes by measuring the expression and activation of +35 key markers of cell state and the concentration change of intracellular metabolites.

During the course of my studies, I always seeked the opportunity to explore different places.
